Most mild cases heal on their own. A few patients get sicker two or three weeks after infection. This is the time when the virus replicates most. After the closure of the city has been gradually infected with disease patients, are facing a serious test

This article was adapted from the Southern People's weekly

By Yang Nan and Kuai Lehao, southern people weekly

Intern journalists, Liu Ruirui, Lei Hanbing, Li Jianqi

More than 3,000 health care workers have been infected since the outbreak began. Zhao Zhigang, deputy director of the Center for First Aid at Zhongnan Hospital of Wuhan University, is one of them.

As early as January 7, Zhao Zhigang and his emergency team had treated a 53 year old patient surnamed Hu. The patient, a vendor at a Huanggang Vegetable Market, was transferred to the Emergency Centre of South Central Hospital after running a high fever. His condition is quite serious. To intubate him, the doctor put his hand into his mouth. The tracheal tube was inserted into his airways, and the patient's sputum spurted out, spattering light-colored foam.

A few days later, all four members of the team fell ill. On January 22, Zhao Zhigang was diagnosed, in order not to occupy the already very tight hospital bed, he volunteered to go home isolation treatment. At 2:00 a.m. on the 23rd, Wuhan declared the city closed.

Watching colleagues into a long and difficult battle, the absence of Zhao Zhigang distraught. As soon as his condition improved, he signed up to join the team of online experts at central South Hospital. He is a patient and a doctor, and he has treated more than 700 patients in just a few days, both in isolation at home and online.

Zhao Zhigang after recovery, isolation treatment, he immediately returned to work, appeared in the emergency room, "the situation is still so severe, treat a is a, I have to live with my conscience. "

Southern People Weekly: Zhongnan Hospital, as one of the "four hospitals" in Wuhan, I heard that your hospital raised the protection level very early.

Zhao Zhigang: we are in the emergency center. On January 8, our ward was requisitioned as an isolation ward. I was head of the ward. The E.R. is multi-system, it's not an infection ward. But it was temporarily activated as a fever ward for infectious diseases. Before that, on December 31 last year, Wuhan announced that all large hospitals in Wuhan would operate 24-hour fever clinics.

Southern People: What was your understanding of the disease at the time?

Zhao Zhigang: we have been talking about the comparison with SARS before. We knew it was different from SARS at the end of December and the beginning of January. There is a flow for the basic treatment of infectious diseases, no management, no hygienist, no public health can do everything right. In the case of a doctor, he can only deal with the patient in front of him. We can not intervene in the whole process of social management.

It was only recently that the whole effort to fight the epidemic took direction and that policy began to fall into place.

Southern People Weekly: you think the previous policy has not landed, why say so?

Zhao Zhigang: is the city sealed? 14 days is a long enough time for an epidemic, if it goes well, there should be a significant drop in the number of new cases, but after 14 days there is no significant improvement. The reason is that it didn't land. People were running around, patients were running around, there were no beds, there were no critical patients, so there was no improvement in mortality.

The current policy is to concentrate all experts, including those from other provinces, on the treatment of the critically ill and to keep the case fatality rate as low as possible because the previous stock is too high.

Southern People: Now there is an opinion among experts that the new coronavirus may be as likely to co-exist with us for a long time as bird flu or flu.

Zhao Zhigang: long-term coexistence is actually acceptable. What is it that we can't accept? The fatality rate is too high. There is too much stock at present. After the closure of the city one after another infected patients, about 14 days to enter the time of serious illness. That is to say, the basic disease of infected people, will be a very short period of serious illness, but the vast majority of patients will focus on two weeks, or even three weeks, before the disease is aggravated. This is the time when the virus has made the most copies. So when the number of patients became too high, it became a number in the tens of thousands -- a history that could not be rewritten, a death rate that could not be brought down if the severity of the disease was not controlled.

Southern People Weekly: Now, the early history of contact with the south China Seafood Market as one of the diagnostic criteria, is not too strict? It's GonNa miss a lot of patients.

Zhao Zhigang: A lot of people in the tangle of diagnostic criteria, diagnostic criteria are generally very rigorous, but the final implementation of the person is alive. At the beginning of the epidemic is in fact "outside loose inside tight" , the result is not tight. Because tight words should be our Wuhan "four big hospitals" set up fever clinic, as far as possible. But no one told the doctor the approximate number of cases. Hospitals don't just open 2,000 beds for infectious diseases. At the time, the numbers were only a few dozen. We were working on 60,70 cases, and it was only January 10th that we were full. With 16 beds in the ICU, 30 beds in the infection department, and 15 beds in the emergency room, over 60 patients were admitted in two days.

Southern People Weekly: later as one of the criteria for the auxiliary diagnosis of CT, it is said that a lot of patients will appear in the CT "white lung" , this "white lung" is the new characteristic of pneumonia it?

Zhao Zhigang: the CT images of this disease are unique and different from other viral infections. It is dominated by subpleural exudation, and then creeping along the bronchial shadow, and then patchy exudation. In Patchy or ground-glass forms, pneumonia from other viral infections or disease-causing agents can develop, but the differences in neocoronary pneumonia are typical.

Southern People Weekly: After the closure of the city, because of insufficient medical strength, once called for home quarantine, resulting in more family clustering of sexual infection, now it seems that home quarantine is not a big problem?

Zhao Zhigang: home segregation is not a big problem, but they are using the wrong way. This disease, 80% of the patients, such as me, is to drink some water, take some medicine can be cured. Antiviral treatment, you choose any antiviral drugs, early can be controlled, the vast majority of patients are mild, can heal.

The main reasons for poor home isolation are: patients are too far away from doctors and nurses, he can not judge when he is sick, he has no place to call for help, public resources are not enough, to see a doctor, found too many patients, simply can not line up, panic. You have a fever for three or four days, you don't have confidence, you don't know medicine, you don't know whether you can live or not, and then everyone goes crazy,

Another big problem is that the Chinese don't know enough about infectious diseases. Propaganda is not in place, social, network support is not enough, resulting in home isolation is not strict. Home isolation requires very strict separation of space, must have a separate sanitation system, you are isolated at home, your family can only take care of you, you can only put food at your door, you have to eat, or go to the toilet, only strictly in your own room, a lot of people can't do that, or they don't have that at home. If it's done, home isolation is fine.

Southern People Weekly: You are also at this stage, sick to participate in the central and Southern Hospital's online expert group, to provide patients with online consultation.

Zhao Zhigang: I was just talking about this with my colleague yesterday. For the prevention and control of public health events, our country's investment is the least, because it does not increase the GDP, is a pure investment-type area. If you look at it in a mature way, you don't have enough upfront investment. How can you expect the system to suddenly meet a public health crisis? Your CDC, your hospital aren't ready for anything, and your team of scientists aren't ready for it. We are still a developing country after all. Like you only have $10 in your pocket. What do you want? Would you go without food, drink, or ten bucks to buy insurance and save it for a doctor's appointment? Of course not. You'd rather bet on yourself not getting sick.

Southern People Weekly: Why are so many health care workers sick in this epidemic? Including Yourself. What happened to you and your colleagues?

Zhao Zhigang: the viral pneumonia, after it enters each section and office in different conditions, each section and office will fall. The rest of the hospital was clean, but in the process, the entire hospital became a contaminated area.

We are a general hospital, the building design is not designed according to infectious disease, there is no way to strictly clean, dirty separate, you in the medical environment of all operations may cause exposure. We don't have an I.C.U. , it's not a negative pressure room, it doesn't have a triple bypass, it doesn't have patient access... even if you don't have contact with the patient, you're in the area, you're sharing a air conditioning, then everyone in this building is at risk of exposure. So now we all turn off the air conditioning and open the windows.

So I told my colleagues, since we can't make a clean zone, we assume that everything is contaminated, and since I can't tell if my colleague is infected, we assume he's already infected. To maintain a distance of two meters, even if the opposite is your relatives, friends, leaders, you have to treat him as a carrier or infectious source.

Southern People Weekly: Why is the judgement patient whether new coronary pneumonia so lag? Is the virus really so cunning after reports of inadequate kits, slow detection, including asymptomatic patients, or false positives and false negatives, and now false negatives?

Zhao Zhigang: our understanding of a new disease is still very flawed. So far, you can't be sure that the person in front of you is 100% NCP, or that the person in front of you is 100% NCP, so there must be 20-30% drift, and that's the science.

Southern People Weekly: What do you feel is a sign of improvement in your case of mild illness?

Zhao Zhigang: When I get to the 8th or 9th day, I feel relaxed. The state of heart and lung function, no longer feel laborious. This disease, 80% of the patients are mild illness, certainly can be good, you can also drink water to be good. Thor Mountain live admission, many patients are their own pots and pans into the, they certainly are not serious illness. Really serious walking is hard, even breathing is very difficult.

Southern People Weekly: a patient told me that one day when she was ill, she suddenly wanted to eat and had an appetite. He felt that he was starting to get better?

Zhao Zhigang: most patients will have a turning point. One day feel very relaxed, may not have a fever that day, may also that day he had diarrhea results not, may be that day his mouth suddenly bitter bitter not bitter. Everyone's symptoms are different, but at some point, he thinks he's getting better.
